OL,3,CLabour and Tories clash over #2,000
OL,4,Ctax claim - so who is right?
OL,6,FThis claim is understood to have come
OL,7,Ffrom produced by the Conservatives,
OL,8,Ftitled Labour Tax Rises and is dated
OL,9,FMay 17. That document makes a series
OL,10,Fof assumptions to estimate the cost
OL,11,Fthat might be attached to potential
OL,12,FLabour policies should they get into
OL,13,Fgovernment.
OL,15,FIt claimed the difference between the
OL,16,Fmoney Labour would raise from its
OL,17,Fpolicies, and the amount it would
OL,18,Fspend, would lead to a deficit of
OL,19,F#38.5 billion over a four-year period.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G6/22
