OL,3,CLabour and Tories clash over #2,000
OL,4,Ctax claim - so who is right?
OL,6,FThe Conservatives say Labour's plans
OL,7,Fto increase the revenue coming into
OL,8,Fthe Treasury would collect #6.2
OL,9,Fbillion a year by 2028/29, therefore
OL,10,Fgenerating #20.4 billion over the next
OL,11,Ffour years.
OL,13,FThe Conservatives argue that this
OL,14,Fwould leave a gap between spending and
OL,15,Ftax revenues of about #10 billion in
OL,16,F2028/29. Spread out over a four-year
OL,17,Fperiod, this figure then reaches the
OL,18,Fcalculated #38.5 billion.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G7/22
