OL,4,Ctax claim - so who is right?
OL,6,FThe document says a Labour government
OL,7,Fwould have the option to raise this
OL,8,Fmoney by increasing taxes, but
OL,9,Falternatively it could borrow to cover
OL,10,Fthe cost.
OL,12,FAccording to the Conservatives, to
OL,13,Ffund this #38.5 billion financial
OL,14,F"black hole" a Labour government would
OL,15,Fhave to implement a tax increase of
OL,16,F#2,094 for every working household.
OL,17,FThis figure is calculated on the basis
OL,18,Fthat there are 18.4 million working
OL,19,Fhouseholds in the UK.
OL,21,FWho carried out the tax calculations?
