OL,6,FAccording to the Tory document, some
OL,7,Fof the estimates have been carried out
OL,8,Fby civil servants at the Treasury
OL,9,Fusing assumptions provided by
OL,10,FConservative Party special advisers.
OL,11,FBut other calculations were not
OL,12,Fprovided by the civil servants.
OL,14,FThe Conservatives claim the figures
OL,15,Fand conclusions were the result of an
OL,16,Fofficial analysis by the Treasury and,
OL,17,Ftherefore, independent of party
OL,18,Fpolitics.
